## Commit Conventions

### Conventional Commits

```
<type>(<scope>): <description>

[optional body]

[optional footer]
```

**Types:**
- `feat:` вЂ” New feature
- `fix:` вЂ” Bug fix
- `docs:` вЂ” Documentation only
- `style:` вЂ” Formatting, no code change
- `refactor:` вЂ” Code restructuring
- `test:` вЂ” Adding/updating tests
- `chore:` вЂ” Build, dependencies

**Examples:**

```bash
feat(auth): add OAuth2 login with Google

fix(api): resolve null pointer in user validation

refactor(database): migrate from MongoDB to PostgreSQL

BREAKING CHANGE: removed deprecated v1 endpoints
```

### Commit Best Practices

| вњ… DO | вќЊ DON'T |
|-------|----------|
| Write in imperative mood | "Fixed bug" в†’ "Fix bug" |
| Keep subject under 50 chars | Long, rambling descriptions |
| Reference issues | No context about why |
| Separate subject from body | Everything in one line |

